  <h2>Tier scope</h2>
  <h3>Free</h3>
  <p>
    3 open tabs at a time. Up to 5 saved snippets. JavaScript, TypeScript, Python, and Ruby runners.
    Monaco editor with syntax highlighting and the keyboard-shortcut editor. No license key
    required — Free is the default install.
  </p>

  <h3>Monthly</h3>
  <p>
    Everything in Free, plus unlimited tabs and snippets, the Go and Rust runners, all 31
    developer utilities, and format-on-save in every supported language. Monthly is a $5/month
    subscription that includes every update while it stays active. Cancel anytime to stop the
    next renewal.
  </p>

  <h3>Pro</h3>
  <p>
    Everything in Monthly, forever. The $59 one-time fee includes 12 months of updates and
    priority email support, with no recurring bill. Renew only if you want another update window;
    your paid entitlement never expires.
  </p>

  <h3>Team</h3>
  <p>
    Everything in Pro, plus seat management and invoicing. $3 per seat per month.
  </p>

  <h3 id="education">Education</h3>
  <p>
    Free Pro for one year, renewable. Open Lingua, go to <em>Settings → License → Educational
    license</em>, and enter your school email. We accept any <code>.edu</code> domain plus
    <code>.ac.uk</code>, <code>.edu.mx</code>, <code>.edu.au</code>, <code>.edu.ca</code>,
    <code>.edu.br</code>, and <code>.ac.in</code>. You'll get a confirmation email with a magic
    link; once clicked, the token arrives by email and pastes itself into the app. Renew from
    the same screen at the end of the year with the same email.
  </p>

  <h3 id="trial">Trial</h3>
  <p>
    14 days of Pro features, no credit card required. Open Lingua, go to <em>Settings →
    License → Try Lingua Pro free for 14 days</em>, enter your email, and click <em>Start
    Trial</em>. The token activates automatically — no manual paste. One trial per email and
    per device.
  </p>

  <h2>How license keys work</h2>
  <p>
    Paid tiers issue a signed token — Ed25519, verified offline against a public key embedded in
    the desktop binary. Lingua does not phone home to validate. The token is bound to a small set
    of devices (currently three for Pro). When you buy a new machine, deactivate the old one from
    Settings → License — the slot frees up immediately.
  </p>

  <h2>Source availability</h2>
  <p>
    The source for the desktop app is published for evaluation, contributor review, and
    transparency about what runs on your machine. You may build the app from source for personal
    non-commercial use. Production or commercial use requires a valid paid tier license. You may
    not redistribute Pro license tokens or the licensing server endpoints.
  </p>
  <p>
    The license is intentionally source-available rather than open-source: it gives you the right
    to read, build, and audit, without giving away the right to redistribute commercial features.
  </p>

  <h2>Refund and transfer</h2>
  <p>
    Refunds within 14 days of purchase, no questions asked. License transfers between machines you
    own are unlimited. Transferring a token to a different person is not permitted — buy a Team
    seat instead.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
